      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(gateway): add agents.setDefault RPC method",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThere is no dedicated Gateway RPC to change the default agent. `agents.list` already returns a read-only `defaultId` and full CRUD exists (`agents.create`/`agents.update`/`agents.delete`), but `agents.update` does not accept a `default` field, so the only way to flip the default is the generic `config.patch` (ADMIN): read the whole config, find the agent's index, build a merge-patch, and reconcile `baseHash`. A \"set as default\" button should not have to reimplement config surgery (openclaw#52928).\n\nThis adds `agents.setDefault` (`{ agentId } -> { ok: true, defaultId }`, scope `operator.admin`). It marks the target as default, clears the flag from every other entry, persists through the same retrying config-write path the other `agents.*` mutations use, and rejects unknown agent ids.\n\n## Why a dedicated method\n\nThe default agent is a per-entry `default?: boolean` flag on `agents.list[]` (`src/config/types.agents.ts:82`), resolved by `resolveDefaultAgentId` (`src/agents/agent-scope-config.ts:91`), which takes the single entry with `default: true` and falls back to the first entry. Nothing exposed a write path for that flag:\n\n- `agents.update`'s param schema is `additionalProperties: false` with no `default` field, so passing `default: true` is rejected.\n- `applyAgentConfig` (`src/commands/agents.config.ts`) merges `name`/`workspace`/`model`/`identity` and never touches `default`.\n\nSo clients were pushed onto `config.patch`, which is exactly the index-lookup + merge-patch + `baseHash` dance the issue calls out.\n\n## Implementation\n\nThe handler mirrors the existing `agents.update`/`agents.delete` shape, so the new surface reuses the same validation, precondition, and retrying-write plumbing rather than inventing a parallel one:\n\n- `setDefaultAgent` (`src/commands/agents.config.ts`): pure transform next to `applyAgentConfig`/`pruneAgentConfig`. Sets `default: true` on the target and `false` on the rest, leaving unchanged entries referentially identical so the persisted config diff stays minimal.\n- `setDefaultAgentConfigEntry` (`agents-config-mutations.ts`): wraps `setDefaultAgent` in `mutateConfigFileWithRetry`, throws `AgentConfigPreconditionError(\"not-found\", id)` for unknown ids, and returns the resolved `defaultId`.\n- `agents.setDefault` handler (`server-methods/agents.ts`): `validateAgentsSetDefaultParams` -> `isConfiguredAgent` guard -> mutation -> `{ ok: true, defaultId }`.\n- Dispatch wiring: descriptor `{ name: \"agents.setDefault\", scope: \"operator.admin\" }` (`core-descriptors.ts`) plus registration in the lazy core handler family list in `server-methods.ts` (next to `agents.update`/`agents.delete`). Both are required: the descriptor advertises and scopes the method, and the lazy list is what makes `handleGatewayRequest` resolve a handler for it. Without the lazy-list entry a live request returns `unknown method: agents.setDefault` even though the descriptor exists.\n\n## Surfaces covered\n\nOne chokepoint per layer, so the method is fully wired and not half-exposed:\n\n- Protocol: `AgentsSetDefaultParams`/`AgentsSetDefaultResult` schemas + types + validator + re-exports (`packages/gateway-protocol/src/...`), and regenerated artifacts (`dist/protocol.schema.json` via `protocol:gen`; tracked Swift `GatewayModels.swift` via `protocol:gen:swift`, +32 additive).\n- Dispatch: core descriptor + lazy core method list in `server-methods.ts`.\n- SDK: `oc.agents.setDefault({ agentId })` (`packages/sdk/src/client.ts`), with the `AgentsSetDefaultParams` type defined next to the sibling agent-mutation params (`packages/sdk/src/types.ts`) and re-exported from the public barrel (`packages/sdk/src/index.ts`) so the helper's imported type resolves and the SDK package typechecks.\n- Admin HTTP RPC: added to the trusted-operator method allowlist (`extensions/admin-http-rpc/src/methods.ts`) so it crosses the HTTP surface like the other `agents.*` mutations.\n- Docs: `docs/gateway/protocol.md` agent-helpers list and `docs/plugins/admin-http-rpc.md` allowlist.\n\nNo new config keys, no migration, no change to `resolveDefaultAgentId`, and `agents.update` keeps its existing field set.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods.agents-set-default-dispatch.test.ts` -> pass. Dispatch-level test: drives the real `handleGatewayRequest` (no `extraHandlers`, so it must resolve through the real lazy registry) and asserts a real request reaches the handler, persists the flip, and rejects unknown agents. Red proof: removing the `agents.setDefault` entry from the lazy list makes all three fail with `unknown method: agents.setDefault`.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/agents.config.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/agents-mutate.test.ts src/gateway/methods/registry.test.ts` -> pass (pure `setDefaultAgent` transform + handler behavior).\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/gateway-protocol` -> 210 passed.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/admin-http-rpc` -> pass, incl. a focused allowlist test (`methods.test.ts`: `agents.setDefault` allowed, unlisted methods rejected) and an HTTP dispatch test that routes `agents.setDefault` through the admin surface.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/sdk/src/index.e2e.test.ts` -> pass. The SDK e2e drives `oc.agents.setDefault({ agentId })` over the in-memory gateway transport and asserts the call reaches the gateway as method `agents.setDefault` with the given params, alongside the existing create/update/delete coverage.\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json` and `-p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json` -> clean (prod + test types). The core tsgo config includes `packages/**`, so this also typechecks the SDK package surface where `AgentsSetDefaultParams` is now defined and exported.\n- `oxfmt --check` + `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs` on all touched files -> clean.\n- Full `pnpm build` not run on this box (memory-constrained); protocol artifacts were regenerated and the Swift diff is purely additive.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: a real Gateway request for `agents.setDefault` crosses the wire, routes through `handleGatewayRequest` and the lazy core registry to the handler, flips the default agent, persists to config, and returns the new `defaultId`; unknown ids are rejected without mutating config.\n\nReal environment tested: a throwaway harness (not committed) stood up a real `ws` WebSocketServer whose every frame is dispatched through the production `handleGatewayRequest`, then connected a real `ws` client and drove the method over the socket against a real on-disk `openclaw.json` (`OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH`), using the real `loadConfig` and `mutateConfigFileWithRetry`. No mocks, no `extraHandlers` override.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: seeded a config with agents `main` (default) and `research`; opened `ws://127.0.0.1:<port>`; sent `{ type: \"req\", method: \"agents.setDefault\", params: { agentId: \"research\" } }` and read the response frame; re-read the file; then sent the same method with an unknown id `ghost`.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```\ntransport: real ws:// WebSocket -> 127.0.0.1:<port> -> handleGatewayRequest\n\n=== BEFORE (on disk) ===\ndefaults: [{\"id\":\"main\",\"default\":true},{\"id\":\"research\",\"default\":false}]\n\n>>> ws send: { method: 'agents.setDefault', params: { agentId: 'research' } }\n<<< ws recv: {\"type\":\"res\",\"id\":\"req-agents.setDefault\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"ok\":true,\"defaultId\":\"research\"}}\n\n=== AFTER (persisted) ===\ndefaults: [{\"id\":\"main\",\"default\":false},{\"id\":\"research\",\"default\":true}]\n\n>>> ws send: agents.setDefault { agentId: 'ghost' }  (unknown agent)\n<<< ws recv: {\"type\":\"res\",\"id\":\"req-agents.setDefault\",\"ok\":false,\"error\":{\"code\":\"INVALID_REQUEST\",\"message\":\"agent \\\"ghost\\\" not found\"}}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: over a real WebSocket, `setDefault research` returns `{ ok: true, defaultId: \"research\" }` and the on-disk config flips `research` to the sole `default: true` entry; an unknown id returns an `INVALID_REQUEST` \"not found\" error and leaves the config untouched. Before the dispatch-list fix, the same frame came back as `unknown method: agents.setDefault`.\n\nWhat was not tested: the SDK's own authenticated `connect` handshake over a production gateway with TLS/auth; the harness exercises the real dispatch and config layers behind the WebSocket, and the SDK wrapper `oc.agents.setDefault` is a one-line passthrough to `agents.setDefault`.\n\n## References\n\n- Closes #52928.\n- Sibling mutations `agents.create`/`agents.update`/`agents.delete` in `src/gateway/server-methods/agents.ts` (same scope, plumbing, and lazy-list registration).\n\n",
        "branch": "feat/agents-set-default-rpc",
